description.narrative: UNICEF country offices in MENA have strengthened access to effective, timely and coordinated technical support to prepare for and respond to needs of women and children affected by humanitarian crises., which contributes to Access To Justice, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Disaster Risk Reduction, Disaster Risk Reduction (Covid), Environmental Sustainability, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Social Protection, Supply And Logistics, Supply And Logistics (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF in the Middle East and North Africa demonstrates strengthened programming excellence for at-scale results for children.

description.narrative: MENARO;ensured timely qualitative responses during refugee influxes in Sudan and Iran and the Gaza conflict. It also developed a preparedness strategy and improved knowledge and accountability against the Core Commitments for Children in Humanitarian Action (CCCs) and Emergency Preparedness Platform benchmarks. MENARO scaled up risk analysis and management support to Iran, Lebanon, Libya, Sudan and Tunisia. After developing an Accountability for Affected Populations (AAP) road map, MENARO now leads AAP innovation efforts. Five countries are piloting the blueprint with the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees, and MENARO is part of the Issue-based Coalitions nexus regional efforts. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:15/12/2021
